Cook and stir onion in 1 Tbsp. of the butter in large skillet on medium heat until tender. Add rice, soup, broccoli and CHEEZ WHIZ; mix lightly. Spoon into 1-1/2-quart casserole. Toss together remaining 1 Tbsp. butter, melted, and bread cubes; sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350 degrees F for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.